Reasoning: The paper focuses on developing network algorithms for function computation in sensor networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication in computer science. The paper specifically discusses dynamic joint aggregation, routing, and scheduling algorithms, which are related to network protocols and algorithms. The paper also introduces a class of functions and characterizes the maximum achievable refresh rate of the network, which involves information theory and optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
